This page is part of a collection assembling links to historical primary sources that are open on the web. It should be seen as a work in progress, and corrections or suggestions for additions are most welcome. These resources may be especially useful to students studying Taiwanese who are looking for inspiration and primary sources for use in their essays who a) are limited to the English language (though some Chinese language sources will also be listed below too) b) lack access to subscription databases that universities with strong East Asia collections may offer, and c) are in lockdown due to a global pandemic.

<strong>Contents</strong>

<a href="#images">Images, Audio, and Film</a>
<a href="#japan">Japanese Reports Related to Colonial Taiwan</a>
<a href="#missionary">Missionary Reports and Minutes</a>
